From: NextOS <noreply@nextos>
Subject: [PATCH] s7d: link IR keymap (custom_maps) + mbox channel on meson-remote

The CoreELEC s7d common dts declares the meson-remote (IR) controller but
never links the IR keymap (custom_maps, already provided by meson-ir-map.dtsi
via meson-s7.dtsi) nor the mailbox channel the SCP firmware uses to deliver the
decoded IR frames. Without them the meson-ir driver logs:
  meson_ir_get_custom_tables:can't find match custom
  can't request mbox
and produces NO input events (the IR remote does nothing in the OS).

Linking custom_maps + the IR mbox channel (7) makes the driver create the
ir_keypad input and emit standard keycodes. Validated on HK1 RBOX X50 (S905X5M):
the factory IR remote navigates and selects (OK = KEY_ENTER, already in the
0x7788 profile of meson-ir-map.dtsi). meson-remote must still be modprobe'd
(it does not autoprobe).
--- a/common_drivers/arch/arm64/boot/dts/amlogic/coreelec_s7d_common.dtsi
+++ b/common_drivers/arch/arm64/boot/dts/amlogic/coreelec_s7d_common.dtsi
@@ -106,6 +106,8 @@
 		reg = <0x0 0xfe084080 0x0 0xA4>, /*Multi-format IR controller*/
 		      <0x0 0xfe084000 0x0 0x58>; /*Legacy IR controller*/
 		interrupts = <GIC_SPI 148 IRQ_TYPE_EDGE_RISING>;
+		map = <&custom_maps>;
+		mboxes = <&mbox_fifo 7>;
 	};
 };
 
